      <section eId="sec_CE-803-1">
        <num>CE 803.1</num>
        <heading>803.1. Â Hearsay exceptions; foreign records of regularly conducted activity</heading>
        <subsection eId="CE-803-1__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>As used in this Article:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CE-803-1__subsec_B__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>&quot;Foreign record of regularly conducted activity&quot; means a memorandum, report, record, or data compilation, in any form, of acts, events, conditions, opinions, or diagnoses, maintained by a business domiciled in a jurisdiction outside the territorial limits of the state of Louisiana.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CE-803-1__subsec_B__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>&quot;Foreign certification&quot; means a written declaration made and signed in a jurisdiction outside the territorial limits of the state of Louisiana by the custodian of a business record of regularly conducted activity or another qualified person that, if falsely made, would subject the maker to criminal penalty under the laws of the state of Louisiana.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CE-803-1__subsec_B__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>&quot;Business&quot; includes a business, institution, association, profession, occupation, and calling of every kind, whether or not conducted for profit.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=508439</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
